frameDefinitions: An Agent causes a Patient to be more strong, often resulting in something that is more secure and safe.
A Sound emitted by a  Sound_source, which construed as a single point, moves along a Path.
An Obstruction blocks an Eclipsed entity partially or completely from view.
An Agent resumes participation in an Activity.
A Destroyer (a conscious entity) or Cause (an event, or an entity involved in such an event) affects the Patient negatively so that the Patient no longer exists.
An Agent causes a Speaker to become silent, sometimes about a particular Topic.
frameExamples: Local Serbs are <t>strengthening</t> their grip on a narrow corridor along the Sava River between two large Serbian areas.
Her shouts <t>echoed</t> around the cylinder formed by the walls.
A small green bulb <t>concealed</t> behind the panel flashed on momentarily .
Normal Service Will Be <t>Resumed</t> Shortly. CNI
